My review is: a semi-finished can, the brand is big, and it tastes not good. If it wasn't for the Harry Potter IP, it would be lucky to sell 240,000 copies, let alone 24 million. Fans' money is so easy to earn. The only thing that can be praised in this game is the portrayal of Sebastian Sallow, who falls into darkness in a way similar to Anakin Skywalker or Arthas Menethil. His voice acting is perfect, and his story is the best in comparison to the others, so it's not hard to see why so many girls are obsessed with him. Well, I kinda like him too... His quality of taking responsibility alone rather than betraying his friend is something I admire, which is why I don't like Ominis Gaunt much, because he vacillates on whether to be loyal to his best friend. But Sebastian's story still has tons of flaws that shouldn't be there, and what particularly annoys me is that I feel like my character is a bi*** in his story. Anyway, if Warner is smart enough, they should support the studio to diligently update this game, improve the player's game experience, release DLC to expand and improve the story and world. Keep JKR away from HL, or she will destroy Slytherin again.
